KernelHook - ARM64 Inline Hook Engine + GUI Framebuffer Overlay

Portable kernel-space hook engine and QEMU virtio-gpu framebuffer
overlay for Android GKI kernels (5.10-6.x), using runtime-only
symbol resolution via /proc/kallsyms (no hardcoded addresses).

Features:
  - DMA physical memory patching + stop_machine atomic hooks
  - Kprobe/kretprobe fallback, hook chaining, BPF integration
  - Markdown-style GUI overlay in kernel space (virtio-gpu/fb)
  - Portable across Android 12-16 GKI (no DRM/fbdev dependency)
  - Procfs and misc device control interface
  - 146/146 user-space tests passing

Build:
  make KERNELDIR=/path/to/kernel/build/dir \
    ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu-

QEMU test (see qemu_test/):
  ./qemu_test/run.sh

